<p>their lunch. The teacher was a young lady &amp; she often rode out from the township on her bike, but when it was raining a gentleman took her in his buggy.</p>
<p>While riding through the bush I often think of the little kids I have left at Myalla, &amp; when I see strong little boys helping their mother chopping wood, or driving in the cows to be milked, or going to the store to bring something, it reminds me of you, &amp; I have not seen any little boy stronger than you, though perhaps some of them may have been cleverer.</p>
<p>Some day you will be able to travel about the country, &amp; I think you will like it very much.</p>
<p>Your Daddy</p>
